WEBVTT

00:07:29.498 --> 00:07:34.252
Creativity seems to emerge
much better from a dark place

00:07:34.276 --> 00:07:35.887
than a joyful place.

00:07:35.911 --> 00:07:38.640
Like, all the best plays
and novels and so forth

00:07:38.664 --> 00:07:41.695
often seem to have been born
out of a form of suffering.

00:07:42.506 --> 00:07:45.117
Those that describe
all being well in the garden

00:07:45.141 --> 00:07:46.995
come over as trite.

00:07:47.436 --> 00:07:48.692
SP: It can,

00:07:48.716 --> 00:07:51.875
although I guess Shakespeare
wrote tragedies and comedies,

00:07:51.899 --> 00:07:53.315
"All's Well That Ends Well."

00:07:53.339 --> 00:07:57.109
So it is possible to have
positive narratives.

00:07:57.133 --> 00:08:00.208
However, an interesting example
of that asymmetry